# Frontend Conventions

## Stack

React 19 + Vite. No router — navigation via component state in `App.jsx` and `Dashboard.jsx`. No UI library.

## Styling

- **Inline `style={{}}` objects** are the primary styling method
- Per-component `<style>` blocks for keyframes and shared classes (`.tab-btn`, `.group-chip`)
- Do not introduce Tailwind, CSS modules, or styled-components without approval
- `index.css` / `App.css` are Vite boilerplate — app UI does not use them

## Design Tokens

| Token | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Background | `#060d14` |
| Text | `#f1f5f9` |
| Accent | `#4ade80` |
| Muted | `#64748b`, `#475569` |
| Heading font | `'Bebas Neue', sans-serif` |
| Body font | `'Rajdhani', sans-serif` |

Load fonts via Google Fonts in component `<style>` blocks (existing pattern).

## UI Patterns

- Mobile-first, portrait PWA layout
- Bottom tab bar: players / teams / games / report / videos
- Hamburger drawer for courts, settings, profile
- Full-screen overlays for LogGame, PlayerProfile, CourtManager, etc.
- Dark theme with glow accents and tier-based aura colors

## Component Structure

- **Hooks** (`src/hooks/`) own data fetching and side effects
- **Components** (`src/components/`) own presentation and local UI state
- Extract sub-components within large files before creating new top-level files
- `racquet-ninja/` is a self-contained partner feature module

## Duplicated Helpers

`getLevel()` (win-based tiers) and avatar wrappers are duplicated across files. When touching these, match the local copy — do not create a shared module unless asked.

## Two Progression Systems

- **Win tiers** (`getLevel`): ROOKIE → CONTENDER → SMASH PRO → ELITE → LEGEND
- **Elo tiers** (`getRatingTier` in `ratingEngine.js`): ROOKIE → BEGINNER → … → LEGEND

Both appear in UI. Do not conflate them.
